<div id="tips" class="container-fluid text-center bg-grey">
  <h2>Tips & Tricks in maintaining hygiene</h2><br>
  <h4>Better to be safe than sorry. Check out some tips we've got for you in keeping safe!</h4>
  <div class="row text-center slideanim">
    <div class="col-sm-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <p><strong>Hand washing</strong></p>
        <p>The easiest way to keep clean! Wash your hands thouroughly with water, apply soap (make sure you lather well!), and then rinse. Do this very often whenever you leave/come back home!</p><br>
        <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/reduce-spread-covid-19-wash-your-hands.html" class="button">Read More >> </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <p><strong>Clean your area!</strong></p>
        <p>We know it's annoying, but clean anything that you have touched outside, such as your phone if you will be taking it up to your room with you. You need to be very careful with who or what you touch these days!</p><br>
        <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/disinfecting-building-facility.html" class="button">Read More >> </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <p><strong>Masks and gloves</strong></p>
        <p>Many people have issues with wearing masks and gloves in public, but it's a precaution to take when interacting in public spaces. You can even make or buy your customized mask. So cool!</p><br>
        	<a href="https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public" class="button">Read More >> </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="symptoms" class="container-fluid text-center">
	<h2>Keep yourself aware</h2>
	<h4>Many of the symptoms for COVID-19 are similar to the flu, so be cautious!</h4>
	<div class="row text-center slideanim">
	    <div class="col-sm-4">
	      <div class="thumbnail">
	        <img src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/08/08/06/52/disease-4392136_960_720.jpg" style="width:80px;height:70px;">
	        <p><strong>Fever and runny nose</strong></p>
	        <p>As soon as you feel a slight fever, be sure to moniter yoursefl for two days. Let your doctor know immediately, they will advise you on the proper steps to take.</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="col-sm-4">
	      <div class="thumbnail">
	        <img src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/08/08/06/53/disease-4392163_960_720.jpg" style="width:80px;height:70px;">
	        <p><strong>Dry cough</strong></p>
	        <p>If your symptoms are getting worse, and you are starting to have dry coughs, call your doctor immediately and keep yourself in isolation. Monitor yourself, and if in two days your symptoms are worse, go to the hospital!</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="col-sm-4">
	      <div class="thumbnail">
	        <img src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/08/08/06/53/disease-4392150_960_720.jpg" style="width:80px;height:70px;">
	        <p><strong>Tiredness</strong></p>
	        <p>Have someone take care of you (of course, while in isolation) and stay in bed. Drink lots of water and keep comfortable. Be sure to book a testing appointment if your symptoms are worse.</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	</div><br>
	<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/symptoms.html" class="button">Learn More >> </a>
</div>

<div id="mental" class="container-fluid text-center bg-grey">
  <h2>Take care of your mental health!</h2>
  <h4>Although it's important to work and study, it's very important to take care of yourself.</h4>
  <div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide text-center" data-ride="carousel">
