<div id="fitness" class="container-fluid">
  <div class="text-center">
    <h2>Finally! Fitness!</h2>
    <h4>Keeping active and fit is the best way to keep healthy. Here are some resources and tips!</h4>
  </div>
  <div class="row slideanim">
    <div class="col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
      <div class="panel panel-default text-center">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h1>Exercise Routines!</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p><strong>Don't worry! You can exercise even at home! Check these out:</strong></p>
		  <ul>
			  <li>10 squats and 10 jumping jacks</li>
			  <li>10 water bottle lifts above the head (dumbbell)</li>
			  <li>4 sets per day!</li>
			  <li>To make it more fun, bring your sibling or friend to workout with you (via  video-calling)!</li>
		  </ul>  
        </div>
        <div class="panel-footer">
          <h3>Do these everyday!</h3>
          <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/fitness-exercises/10-best-exercises-everyday" class="btn btn-log">Read More!</a>
        </div>
      </div>      
    </div>     
    <div class="col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
      <div class="panel panel-default text-center">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h1>Eat Healthy!</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>Eating healthy is one of the most important aspects when keeping fit. If you're looking to loose weight, don't stop eating, just eat the right food in the right ammounts. Same goes for gaining weight! To ensure you're eating the right portions of good foods, keep your body type in mind! Call your doctor and plan a good diet to follow to ensure that you can follow-up on everything you're eating and in what portions. Stay away from eating too much 'junk', and NEVER eat right after a workout!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-footer">
          <h3>Plan your diet!</h3>
          <a href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/healthy-eating-for-beginners" class="btn btn-log">Read More!</a>
        </div>
      </div>      
    </div>       
